  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-9 clean)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels. One explicitly-flagged gap in model-form confidence is documented with full rationale and accepted as residual risk supported by independent experimental corroboration. Decision: Accepted.",
