      "rationale": "The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model is the most widely validated model for centrifugal blood pump NIH prediction in the published literature. Model-form uncertainty is explicitly quantified: the power-law exponent α has a documented ±15% uncertainty (1σ) based on inter-laboratory calibration data, which is the dominant contributor to the ±38% NIH prediction interval identified in sensitivity analysis. This gap is honestly documented. Despite the acknowledged uncertainty, the model consistently predicts conservative (upper-bound) NIH values relative to bench measurements across all five operating points, and all upper-bound predictions remain below the clinical threshold. The conservative bias is mechanistically explained by the model's over-prediction of shear exposure in recirculation zones.",
